HEADWORD: Owenite
<hw>Ow"en*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A follower of
<person>Robert <etsep>Owen</etsep></person>, who tried to reorganize
society on a socialistic basis, and established an industrial community
on the Clyde, Scotland, and, later, a similar one in Indiana.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

